Yemen café ALWAYS hits the spot and NEVER disappoints! Service is great, the guys are attentive and bring you salad, soup and bread within minutes of arriving. The one dish I order every time no matter what is Fasoolia, which is a white bean dish that's is so savory and pairs amazingly with the bread they give you. We also ordered Lamb Haneeth to share and that was also amazing. The rice is always prefect and the 5-hr slow-cooked lamb literally fell off the bone; plenty for two considering we also had the salad, soup, beans and bread. We had the complimentary water in aluminum cups, which to me tastes better than bottled water, and closed off our meal with a delicious complimentary tea (self-serve) with a touch of milk, great palate cleanser. I've tried both locations, with the one at Atlantic Ave being the original, and they both get 5 starts from me!

Absolutely delicious! Restaurant was clean and well-staffed, wait-staff was super friendly, and the food was outstanding. Everything from the soup and naan to the entrees was great. The famous stand-out dish is the lamb haneeth. Quite possibly the most tender meat I have ever tasted; the rich lamb flavor literally melts in your mouth like butter it is so soft. I also enjoyed the lamb fahsah immensely; the food stayed so hot in the clay bowl, and the flavors were exceptional. The silky texture of the shredded lamb was to die for. My sister ordered a vegetarian dish, which was seasoned similarly to the lamb dishes the rest of my family ordered, and was equally good. Overall, cannot wait to go back. This may be the best restaurant in Bay Ridge!

(Translated by Google) Surprisingly, I would recommend this restaurant for other dishes than the main courses: the lamb soup, offered as an appetizer, is excellent. The tea, also offered at the end, is comforting. But above all, hummus dishes (the one with meat such as vegetarian) are absolutely delicious, and it is a demanding Lebanese who speaks. They are called appetizers but as stall as a main course (the plate is huge and reflects the generosity of the restaurant!). Nevertheless, the Yemeni dishes themselves are quite disappointing: lamb haneeth like chicken haneeth are very correct from the point of view of cooking, but are bland and basic. It is "only" meat accompanied by rice, without sauce. The bread is good, but nothing exceptional.  I will gladly come back for their hummus and soup.  (Original) Etonnament, je recommanderais ce restaurant pour les autres mets que les plats principaux : la soupe à l’agneau, offerte en entrée, est excellente. Mais surtout, les plats de hoummous (celui accompagné de viande comme le végétarien) sont absolument succulents, et c’est une libanaise exigente qui parle. Ils sont qualifiés d’appetizers mais calent autant qu’un plat principal (l’assiette est énorme et témoigne de la générosité du restaurant !). Néanmoins, les plats à proprement parler yéménites sont assez décevants : le lamb haneeth comme le chicken haneeth sont très corrects du point de vue de la cuisson, mais sont fades et basiques.
